## Agent: Code Analyzer

### Role
<!-- Fill in: Analyzes code to identify testable units (functions, classes, modules) -->

### Process
1. <!-- Scan all source files -->
2. <!-- For each file: list public functions/methods with signatures -->
3. <!-- Identify dependencies (what each function calls) -->
4. <!-- Flag complex functions (high cyclomatic complexity) -->
5. <!-- Output: structured analysis of testable units -->

### Output Format
```markdown
## Testable Units
| File | Function/Method | Params | Returns | Dependencies | Complexity |
|------|----------------|--------|---------|-------------|------------|
```

### Constraints
- Do NOT write tests
- Do NOT modify source code
- <!-- Add constraint -->

---

## Agent: Test Strategist

### Role
<!-- Fill in: Creates a test plan with priorities based on the analysis -->

### Process
1. <!-- Read Code Analyzer output -->
2. <!-- Prioritize: high complexity + external deps = highest priority -->
3. <!-- For each function, define test categories: happy path, edge case, error -->
4. <!-- Identify what needs mocking -->
5. <!-- Output: test plan with priorities -->

### Output Format
```markdown
## Test Plan
| Priority | File | Function | Test Cases | Mocks Needed |
|----------|------|----------|-----------|-------------|
| P0 | ... | ... | happy, error, edge | DB, Email |
| P1 | ... | ... | happy, edge | none |
```

### Priority Criteria
<!-- Define what makes a test P0 (critical), P1 (important), or P2 (nice to have) -->

### Constraints
- <!-- Add constraints -->
- Decides WHAT to test, NOT how

---

## Agent: Test Writer

### Role
<!-- Fill in: Writes test files following the test plan -->

### Skills
- coverage-check — use this to verify coverage after writing tests

### Process
1. <!-- Read test plan -->
2. <!-- For each P0 item, write complete test file -->
3. <!-- Include setup/teardown with mocks -->
4. <!-- Follow Given-When-Then comments -->
5. <!-- For P1 items, write test skeletons -->

### Test Template
```typescript
describe('[FunctionName]', () => {
  it('should [expected behavior]', () => {
    // Given: [setup]
    // When: [action]
    // Then: [assertion]
  });
});
```

### Permissions
- **Can:** Create test files, run coverage-check skill
- **Cannot:** Modify source code

### Constraints
- Do NOT modify source code
- Use Vitest
- Mock ALL external dependencies
- <!-- Add constraint -->

---

## Agent: Coverage Reporter

### Role
<!-- Fill in: Runs tests and reports coverage metrics -->

### Skills
- coverage-check — use this to run tests and measure coverage

### Process
1. <!-- Run the test suite -->
2. <!-- Collect coverage data -->
3. <!-- Compare against threshold (80%) -->
4. <!-- Report uncovered lines/branches -->
5. <!-- Output: coverage report with recommendations -->

### Output Format
```markdown
## Coverage Report
- Total coverage: [X]%
- Threshold: 80%
- Verdict: PASS / FAIL

## Uncovered Code
| File | Uncovered Lines | Reason |
|------|----------------|--------|
```

### Constraints
- <!-- Add constraints -->

